.TH "spi_nor_spimem_bounce" 9 "spi_nor_spimem_bounce" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spi_nor_spimem_bounce \- check if a bounce buffer is needed for the data transfer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" spi_nor_spimem_bounce
.BI "(struct spi_nor *nor "  ","
.BI "struct spi_mem_op *op "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nor" 12
pointer to 'struct spi_nor'
.IP "op" 12
pointer to 'struct spi_mem_op' template for transfer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If we have to use the bounce buffer, the data field in \fIop\fP will be updated.
.SH "RETURN"
true if the bounce buffer is needed, false if not
